ioctl( ) : Input-Output Control.
It is a system call available with most of the driver categories.
For example : Volume control for audio device or display configuration for video device.
Format : 
       int ioctl(struct inode *i, struct file *f, unsigned int cmd, unsigned long arg);
       long ioctl(struct file *f, unsigned int cmd, unsigned long arg);
-ENOTTY : "No such ioctl for device".\ and does not offer an ioctl entry point.
